Class Description: Autoclave-resistant piggyback labels for thermal-transfer printers. These removable labels have a unique label-on-label design, perfect for identifying multiple linked items and surfaces. They withstand multiple steam autoclave sterilization cycles, ideal for labeling reusable sterilization containers.

Class Title: Thermal-Transfer Cryogenic Labels for Frozen Vials & Surfaces with SimPEEL™ Technology (Patent Pending)
Class Description: Thermal-transfer cryo labels provide an all-in-one solution for cryo storage that can firmly adhere to ambient and already frozen surfaces, without the need for thawing, cure time, or any other special treatment. The addition of SimPEEL technology allows these labels to be peeled from their liner quickly with an adhesive-free tab that ensures they will not stick to your hands or gloves.
Containers: Tubes & Vials,Frozen Vials & Surfaces,Cryo Boxes,Sterilization Material

Class Title: Autoclave-Resistant Thermal-Transfer Labels with SimPEEL Technology
Class Description: Permanent autoclave-resistant labels with our SimPEEL technology for effortless peeling and application. Perfect for use in steam autoclaves, dry heat ovens, gamma irradiators, and ethylene oxide gas sterilizers, these sterilization labels are intended for identifying various containers and surfaces that will undergo sterilization, such as plastic bags, blister packs, and various glass or plastic labware.

Class Title: Permanent Labels for Autoclave & High Temperatures
Class Description: Self-laminating permanent labels that resist high temperatures and sterilization procedures, including in steam autoclaves and dry heat ovens. The clear laminate also provides added protection against abrasion and spraying or wiping with alcohol and surface sanitizing wipes. Printable with all common thermal-transfer printers.

Class Title: Steam Sterilization Indicator Thermal-Transfer Labels
Class Description: These permanent autoclave-resistant labels include an indicator strip that noticeably changes color (from white to charcoal gray) when the labels have been autoclaved. This allows autoclaved material to be quickly and easily identified, eliminating the need for additional autoclave sterilization tape. SAUP-class labels can also be printed with variable text and barcodes using thermal-transfer printers

Class Title: Deep-Freeze RFID Labels for Plates
Class Description: Thermal-transfer RFID labels for microplates, Petri dishes, as well as skirted and semi-skirted high- and low-profile PCR plates. Their integrated RFID inlay allows multiple plates to be scanned simultaneously, suitable for real-time tracking and managing the inventory of multiple plates used in high-throughput screening. Can be printed and encoded with thermal-transfer RFID printers.

Class Title: Deep-Freeze Labels for DYMO® LabelWriter™ 450-Series (Patent Pending)
Class Description:
Freezer-grade labels designed for labeling various containers stored in low temperature freezers, refrigerators, cold rooms, or transported on dry ice. These DYMO-compatible are supplied in a clear format that will not obscure the container’s contents, ensuring they remain clearly visible. They also tolerate elevated temperatures, suitable for identifying cell culture flasks and plates stored in incubators.

Not compatible with DYMO® LabelWriter™ 5-Series (550, 550 Turbo, 5XL)

Class Title: Transparent Cryogenic Laser Labels for Frozen Vials
Class Description: Our LCY-class laser labels for frozen surfaces are transparent, providing a “printed-on” effect, without concealing the surface or content underneath. Can be applied under deep-freeze conditions, they withstand prolonged storage in cryogenic conditions, as well as elevated temperatures, high humidity conditions, and thawing in heated water baths. Printable with office and desktop laser printers, free templates are available for easy set-up.

Class Title: Cryogenic Laser Labels for Frozen Surfaces
Class Description: LCB-class laser CryoSTUCK® labels are laser printable cryogenic labels specifically designed to conceal pre-existing information, ideal as an over-label for frozen containers and vials where thawing the sample is not recommended. They also withstand elevated temperatures, suitable for use in heat-based sterilization processes.

Class Title: Laser & Inkjet Matte Paper Removable Labels
Class Description: Our removable RLZP-class labels are compatible with both desktop laser and inkjet printers. Ideal for general use applications in labs and offices to identify files, folders, boxes, and containers. These paper labels can be readily repositioned and removed without leaving behind any adhesive residue. Free MS Word templates are available for easy formatting.

Class Title: Autoclave-Resistant Labels for Inkjet Printers
Class Description: Autoclave-resistant labels for desktop inkjet printers. Can be printed with eye-catching full-color logos and graphics. These permanent inkjet labels will adhere to glass, plastic, and metal surfaces, perfect for identifying various sterilization containers and materials. They can be easily formatted for printing using our free online MS Word templates.

Class Title: Cryogenic Automation Labels for Barcode Labelers
Class Description: Cryogenic automation labels, compatible with most automated print-and-apply systems. Designed to withstand long-term storage in liquid nitrogen (-196°C) and laboratory freezers (-80°C), these permanent labels can be printed with all major thermal-transfer automated labeling system brands.

Class Title: Permanent Autoclave-Resistant Thermal-Transfer Labels
Class Description: Permanent autoclave-resistant labels withstand various sterilization procedures, including in steam autoclaves, dry heat ovens, gamma irradiators, and ethylene oxide gas sterilizers. These thermal-transfer printable heat-resistant labels will adhere to a variety of surfaces such as metal, plastic, and glass, perfect for identifying sterilization containers, surgical tools and trays, as well as labware that will undergo sterilization.

Class Title: Autoclave-Resistant Labels for Laser Printers
Class Description: Our A4AKA-class laser labels have a permanent adhesive, perfect for identifying disposable sterilization pouches and bags. Provided in A4 sheet format for printing with most common desktop laser printers, they can be printed with human-readable text, serialized numbering, as well as 1D/2D barcodes. Can be easily formatted for printing using our free online MS Word templates.

Class Title: Heat-Resistant Labels for DYMO® LabelWriter™ 450-Series (Patent Pending)
Class Description: EDAP-class labels are compatible with DYMO 450 and 4XL LabelWriter® printers and can withstand elevated temperatures in dry (ovens) and wet (water baths) conditions. Unlike other direct thermal labels, they will not turn entirely dark when exposed to high-heat conditions, perfect for labeling various containers or devices destined for high-heat applications.

Class Title: Laser & Inkjet Glossy Paper labels
Class Description: Our general-use LGP-class paper labels are compatible with both desktop laser and inkjet printers. Perfect for use in various applications in the lab, offices, and warehouse, these permanent labels can be easily customized using our free online templates.

Class Title: Cryogenic Thermal-Transfer Labels for Metal Racks
Class Description: Our transparent cryogenic AWC-class labels are intended for identifying metal surfaces stored in cryogenic conditions, including in liquid nitrogen Dewars. Ideal for labeling aluminum cryogenic vial canes, metal racks for cryo and freezer boxes, and metal goblets for cryo straws. Their clear design also makes them ideal for labeling tools and equipment with unique designs and logos, providing a direct “printed-on” effect.

Class Title: Self-Laminating Thermal-Transfer Labels for Microscope Slides
Class Description: Xylene and solvent-resistant labels designed for identifying slides throughout harsh staining protocols, including immunohistochemistry procedures and the antigen retrieval process. Compatible with fully automated, multi-slide processors and stainers, these durable labels can withstand long-term exposure to solvents, acidic/basic buffers, as well as high temperature processes.

Class Title: Deep-Freeze Labels for High-Profile PCR Tube Strips
Class Description: These clear PCR labels are designed to quickly and accurately identify PCR tube strips with separable individual sub-labels. Freezer and thermocycler-safe, these thermal-transfer printable labels allow each individual tube of a PCR strip to be accurately labeled while ensuring the contents remain fully visible.

Class Title: Peel & Reveal FrozenSTUCK™ – Labels for Extended Content and Frozen Surfaces (Patent Pending)
Class Description: User-printable using common thermal printers to provide a fully printable area suitable for extended content (e.g. multiple languages, instructions for use, regulatory requirements, etc.). They are intended to adhere in an overlapping fashion onto already frozen plastic tubes and glass vials at -80°C (-112°F), and for long-term storage in ultra-low temperature freezers (-80°C/-112°F) and transportation on dry ice. These labels withstand common sanitizing procedures including alcohol wiping.

Class Title: Metal-Detectable Thermal-Transfer Labels for Paraffin Wax Blocks
Class Description: Intended for hard-to-stick surfaces, these solvent-resistant labels are provided with a unique metallic foil layer, allowing them to be detected using a metal detector. When used with an appropriate lab waste screening program, these thermal-transfer labels help reduce the accidental loss of valuable samples in high-throughput labs. Ideal for labeling paraffin wax blocks commonly used in histology applications.

Class Title: Solvent-Resistant Removable Blackout Labels
Class Description: Removable blackout labels are designed to conceal pre-existing information and labels. Resistant to spraying with chemicals and solvents, such as xylene and alcohol, these labels are ideal for re-identifying slides marked with unclear, erroneous, or incomplete information. SBOR-class labels also have a glove-friendly adhesive that ensures the labels can be easily removed without damaging the information underneath.

Class Title: Direct Thermal Cryo Labels for Frozen Vials & Surfaces with SimPEEL™ Technology (Patented)
Class Description: Direct thermal printable cryogenic labels for already frozen surfaces. Our unique SimPEEL technology makes these cryo labels easy to peel and apply, even on frozen surfaces. Ideal for identifying valuable, temperature-sensitive samples and specimen that cannot be thawed before labeling. Can be printed with most direct thermal printers, requiring no additional ink sources for printing.

Class Title: Permanent Self-Laminating Thermal-Transfer Labels
Class Description: These self-laminating permanent labels are intended for identifying equipment, dishware, animal cages, and other material requiring protection against water, brushing and scrubbing, soap, disinfectants, and other harsh chemicals. Thermal-transfer printable, once laminated, the information is protected and cannot be altered.

Class Title: Cryogenic Labels for Direct Thermal Barcode Printers
Class Description: Permanent direct thermal cryo labels for vials, microtubes, microplates, freezer boxes, and plastic bags. These barcode labels withstand long-term storage in cryogenic conditions, including in liquid nitrogen and ultra-low temperature freezers, and will not crack or peel, even through multiple freeze-thaw cycles.

Class Title: Automated Labels for Barcode Labelers
Class Description: Cryogenic automation labels, compatible with most automated print-and-apply printers and labelers. MHBTT-class labels are designed to withstand long-term storage in liquid nitrogen (-196°C) and laboratory freezers (-80°C) and will also withstand exposure to harsh chemicals. Can be printed with all major thermal-transfer automated labeling systems.

Class Title: Water Dissolvable Paper Labels for DYMO® LabelWriter™ 450-Series
Class Description: These paper labels will completely disintegrate when exposed to water and simple hand or mechanical rubbing. Compatible with DYMO 450 and 4XL printers, these water dissolvable labels are perfect for labeling containers subject to frequent washing, requiring no additional effort to remove. Simply wash them off, and relabel to maintain a fresh-looking appearance.

Class Title: Blackout Cryo Laser Labels for Frozen Surfaces
Class Description: Supplied in A4 sheet format for printing in standard desktop laser printers, these A4LCB-class laser CryoSTUCK® labels are specifically designed to conceal pre-existing information on frozen containers and vials where thawing the sample is not recommended. Free templates are available for quick set-up.

Class Title: Cryogenic & Autoclave-Resistant Self-Laminating Laser Labels
Class Description: A4DFSL-class labels provided in A4 sheet format for desktop laser printers withstand long-term cryo storage in liquid nitrogen and deep-freeze conditions, as well as sterilization in steam autoclaves. These wrap-around laser labels also resist abrasion, scratching, as well as spraying and wiping with chemicals and detergents.

Class Title: Cryogenic Laser Labels for Metal Racks
Class Description: AWL-class cryo labels for metal surfaces are intended for long-term storage in liquid nitrogen (-196°C), ultra-low temperature freezers (-80°C), and dry ice transportation. Perfect for identifying metal racks, sleeves and canes, as well as other metal surfaces and containers. Compatible with most desktop laser printers, free MS Word templates are available for quick setup and printing.

Class Title: Removable Deep-Freeze Labels for Automated Print & Apply Systems
Class Description: Removable labels, designed for use with automated print-and-apply barcode systems to identify vials, tubes, as well as microplates. These deep-freeze labels withstand a range of temperatures, perfect for use throughout the lab, including for long-term storage in lab freezers or in incubators. MRMTT-class labels are thermal-transfer printable.

Class Title: Cryogenic Labels for Frozen Surfaces with SimPEEL™ Technology for DYMO® LabelWriter™ 450-Series (Patent Pending)
Class Description:
Direct thermal printable cryogenic labels for already frozen surfaces compatible with the 450 series and 4XL DYMO LabelWriter printers. Provided with our unique SimPEEL technology, they can be easily and quickly peeled from their liner and applied to already frozen vials and tubes (-80°C), prior to storage in liquid nitrogen (-196°C) and lab freezers. These cryo labels also display excellent resistance to routinely used laboratory chemicals and surface-sanitizing wipes.

Not compatible with DYMO® LabelWriter™ 5-Series (550, 550 Turbo, 5XL)

Class Title: Transparent Cryogenic Labels for Thermal-Transfer Printers
Class Description: These thermal-transfer cryogenic labels resist a wide range of temperatures, from extreme low temperatures, including storage in liquid nitrogen (-196°C), to elevated temperatures, such as boiling water (+100°C). They also have a Transparent design that ensures the contents and surface of labeled containers remain visible.

Class Title: Cryogenic Labels for DYMO® LabelWriter™ 450-Series
Class Description:
These DYMO-compatible cryo labels are perfectly suited for identifying microtubes, cryo vials, and cryo/freezer boxes that will be stored under cryogenic conditions, including in liquid phase and vapor phase liquid nitrogen (-196°C). Printable with the DYMO 450-series of LabelWriter® printers, these labels do not require ribbons or additional ink sources for printing.

Not compatible with DYMO® LabelWriter™ 5-Series (550, 550 Turbo, 5XL)

Class Title: Cryogenic RFID Labels for Thermal-Transfer Printers
Class Description: Cryogenic RFID labels for cryo vials, microtubes, cryo/freezer boxes, and other cryo containers destined for storage in liquid nitrogen (-196°C), lab freezers (-80°C), or dry ice transport. They can be scanned/read without the need for a direct line-of-sight, even when in liquid nitrogen. Can be printed and encoded using a thermal-transfer RFID printer.

Class Title: Autoclave-Resistant RFID Thermal-Transfer Labels
Class Description: Autoclave-resistant RFID labels for the identification of sterilization containers that will undergo steam and dry heat sterilization. These thermal-transfer labels have an RFID inlay for enhanced tracking, by combining printed visual information with encoded RFID data. Compatible with handheld, fixed, and integrated UHF RFID readers, these permanent labels can be integrated with sterilization management systems.

Class Title: Removable Cryogenic Labels for Laser Printers
Class Description: Removable cryo labels provided in A4 sheet format for printing with laser printers. Ideal for long-term storage in liquid-phase and vapor phase liquid nitrogen (-196°C), freezers (-80°C), and on dry ice. Their glove-friendly adhesive ensures the labels can be removed easily without leaving any residue behind. Can be printed with desktop laser printers and inscribed with permanent markers. MS Word templates are available for easy formatting.

Class Title: Cryogenic Labels for Laser Printers
Class Description: Permanent cryogenic laser labels designed for 0.2 ml PCR tubes. These freezer-grade labels are thermocycler-safe, perfect for use In PCR thermocyclers, as well as subsequent storage in lab freezers. Laser printable, they can also be inscribed with permanent markers. MS Word templates are available for easy formatting.

Class Title: Cryogenic Thermal-Transfer RFID Labels for Frozen Tubes & Vials
Class Description: Cryogenic RFID labels for labeling already frozen surfaces and vials without the need to thaw them first (-80°C). In addition, their integrated RFID inlay allows multiple vials to be scanned simultaneously, without a direct line-of-sight, helping to maintain sample integrity. Designed to withstand prolonged storage in cryogenic conditions, including in liquid nitrogen Dewars (-196°C).

Class Title: Inkjet Labels for Deep-Freeze Storage
Class Description: A4 sheet format deep-freeze labels for desktop inkjet printers can be printed with eye-catching color logos, graphics, images, and data, or written on with ballpoint pens and cryogenic markers. Designed to identify vials, tubes, plastic bags, freezer boxes, plates, and other containers for storage in low temperature lab freezers and dry ice transportation.

Class Title: Xylene-Resistant RFID Labels for Paraffin Wax Blocks
Class Description: Chemical-resistant RFID labels for short- and long-term storage of Formalin-Fixed Paraffin-Embedded (FFPE) tissue blocks. Ideal for accurate and quick identification of tissue-embedded cassettes, improving cassette management, and enhanced tracking. These thermal-transfer RFID labels are specifically designed to integrate with specimen management systems.

Class Title: Wrap-Around Cryogenic RFID Thermal-Transfer Labels
Class Description: These self-laminating cryo labels combine RFID technology with a clear wrap-around laminate to ensure your cryo vials are securely identified with visual and electronic information. This transparent laminate protects the printed information from extreme temperatures, chemicals, such as alcohols and detergents, as well as abrasion and scratching. Compatible with handheld, fixed, and integrated RFID readers.

Class Title: Cryogenic Labels with SimPEEL™ Technology for DYMO® LabelWriter™ 450-Series (Patent Pending)
Class Description:
DYMO-compatible cryogenic labels with our SimPEEL technology, making them easy to peel from their liner and apply on the intended surface. Designed to withstand long-term storage in ultra-low temperature freezers (-80°C) and liquid nitrogen (-196°C), perfect for identifying cryo vials, tubes, and boxes. Printable with the 450-series of DYMO LabelWriter printers.

Not compatible with DYMO® LabelWriter™ 5-Series (550, 550 Turbo, 5XL)
